cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.CG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a long-standing open problem in formal language theory, specifically the decidability of equivalence of deterministic top-down tree-to-string transducers. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents efficient algorithms for subclasses of the problem. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses techniques from multi-linear algebra to obtain the efficient algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of the algorithms presented. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of inductive invariants, which can be relevant in computational geometry.
